1
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,250
[SUN] Thank you, Mother,
and thank you father.

2
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,708
Thank you for always lookin'
after me for all of these years.

3
00:00:31,791 --> 00:00:35,666
Now I, Sun Seto, now I am--

4
00:00:44,083 --> 00:00:45,541
[NARRATOR]
Beneath the gently rolling

5
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:47,625
waves of the Seto Inland Sea.

6
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:51,291
Young Nagasumi's life is saved,
and forever changed.

7
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:55,000
But as with any debt,
this one too must be repaid.

8
00:00:55,083 --> 00:00:56,833
So our story begins.

9
00:00:56,916 --> 00:01:01,416
Please humor them with a smile,
for young love is never easy.

10
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:08,708
♪

11
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:39,208
[TV HOST]
Now Lunar, you're still in

12
00:02:39,291 --> 00:02:40,875
junior high, isn't that right?

13
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:41,875
[LUNAR] Yes.

14
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:43,291
It must be rather
tough for you to

15
00:02:43,375 --> 00:02:45,541
balance your studies along
with a big singing career.

16
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:47,416
Yes, it is, but you
can't be a pop star

17
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,208
unless you're willing
to do a balancing act.

18
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:50,500
Did you hear
that, everybody?

19
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:52,875
Isn't this little girl
really something?

20
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:54,875
Wow, Lunar, on television,

21
00:02:54,958 --> 00:02:57,500
you're a hundred times
cuter than in real life.

22
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
What you meant to
say was that in real life,

23
00:03:01,083 --> 00:03:02,750
we're a million times cuter
than we are on television.

24
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:05,500
[NAGASUMI] Yeah, of
course that's what I meant.

25
00:03:06,416 --> 00:03:08,208
[LUNAR] Hand us
that remote, Nagasumi.

26
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:09,375
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Her fans are lucky

27
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:10,583
that they never
have to see this.

28
00:03:10,666 --> 00:03:12,166
[MOM] ♪ I love doing
the dishes with my ♪

29
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:14,083
♪ daughter in my
sparkling kitchen! ♪

30
00:03:14,166 --> 00:03:16,708
♪ What a wonderful way to
spend a lazy Sunday afternoon! ♪

31
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:18,791
Ya seem like you're havin'
a whole lot of fun, Mother.

32
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:20,916
Of course I'm happy.
Why wouldn't I be?

33
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,541
I feel like one of my lifelong
dreams has finally come true.

34
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:26,083
I've wanted a daughter for
as long as I can remember.

35
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:27,541
Thank you so much.

36
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:30,166
Just hearin' ya say that makes
me feel happy too, ya see.

37
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:32,833
I mean sons really
are no good, are they?

38
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:35,291
Hearing that
doesn't make me happy.

39
00:03:35,375 --> 00:03:37,083
[MOM] I admit I was
devastated when

40
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:38,750
our house was destroyed, but...

41
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,291
I guess it turned
out all right since

42
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:42,166
Lunar's father is in the
construction business.

43
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:43,666
You can say that again!

44
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,375
The most modern
kitchen available,

45
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:47,000
and with all electric
appliances, too!

46
00:03:47,083 --> 00:03:49,125
Only the very best!

47
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,750
I don't know what
you're so excited about.

48
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:53,083
At our estate, all of this stuff
would be handled by servants.

49
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,416
Ya've got it
all wrong, Lunar.

50
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,541
That isn't the point.

51
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:56,791
[LUNAR]
What's the point?

52
00:03:56,875 --> 00:03:59,000
Ya see, this is part
of my bridal trainin'.

53
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,333
Training?

54
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:02,125
I'm marryin' into a
dry-land family, after all.

55
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,375
So I have to learn to do all the

56
00:04:03,458 --> 00:04:05,333
work Mother does
around the house.

57
00:04:05,958 --> 00:04:07,583
[MOM] What a fine bride she is.

58
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:11,000
Too bad she's wasted
on the men of my family.

59
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:12,875
What an old
fashioned attitude.

60
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,833
Those ideals are tres passé.

61
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,541
I dunno what language
yer speakin',

62
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:19,083
but man is a ship and
woman is his harbor.

63
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:21,875
See Lunar, it's a wife's
duty to protect the home.

64
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:23,166
You're behind the times.

65
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,458
Are you sure you were
born in the nineties?

66
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:27,583
Now, now girls, there
is no reason for fighting.

67
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:30,666
It's okay...
you can disagree.

68
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:33,625
Come on Sun, it's time
to go shopping for dinner.

69
00:04:33,708 --> 00:04:35,125
Okay!

70
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:36,875
We've got to give today's
meal all the effort we've got!

71
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:38,041
Yeah!

72
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:39,875
Hey Lunar, do you
wanna come with us?

73
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:41,750
[LUNAR] No,
I sure don't.

74
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:43,041
Wonder why not.

75
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:44,833
Lunar's probably
tired from working

76
00:04:44,916 --> 00:04:47,041
so hard singing
and going to school.

77
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:51,083
Oh I see, so Lunar's
a ship instead of a harbor.

78
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,583
[MOM] Look after the
place while we're gone!

79
00:04:53,666 --> 00:04:55,500
[LUNAR] Yeah, yeah.

80
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,333
[TV HOST] I understand you
have a new album coming out?

81
00:04:56,416 --> 00:04:57,458
[NAGASUMI] Seriously, Lunar.

82
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:58,958
You should've gone
shopping with them.

83
00:04:59,041 --> 00:05:01,041
Why didn't you
just drop the act?

84
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:03,416
Drop what act?

85
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,541
[NAGASUMI] Wasn't it one?

86
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:06,041
[LUNAR] Of course
it wasn't an act.

87
00:05:06,125 --> 00:05:07,958
Quit trying to pretend like
you actually know something,

88
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:09,333
manservant,
and learn your place.

89
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:11,916
My crotch is in some
serious trouble here!

90
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,208
Well, never
mind all that now.

91
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:18,375
'Cause you see...

92
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:21,416
We're finally alone
in an empty house.

93
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:22,958
How can you talk to
me all sweet and cute

94
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:25,166
like that and give me the
Grinder at the same time?

95
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:27,833
[LUNAR] I was just thinking...
We live together, but we've

96
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:30,625
never been all
alone before, right?

97
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:32,625
I've been waiting
for this moment.

98
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:34,166
Well, that's a shock!

99
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,458
[NAGASUMI] Lunar seems to be
radiating this incredible charm.

100
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:38,250
But why? What does
she want to do?

101
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,416
Why does she want to be alone?

102
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:42,125
Want to go
up to my room?

103
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:44,000
Up the stairs
to adulthood.

104
00:05:45,916 --> 00:05:47,791
[DAD] I can't tell you
how upsetting it was

105
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:49,208
when our house was
destroyed last week.

106
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:50,875
Thanks for your
help fixing it up.

107
00:05:50,958 --> 00:05:52,875
It was no problemo.

108
00:05:52,958 --> 00:05:54,750
It gave ya an excuse
to see yer daughter,

109
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,166
didn't it, Edomae?

110
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,916
So I bet from your end it
was all fer the best, huh?

111
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,125
You can just visit.

112
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:00,916
You don't need a
complicated excuse for it.

113
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,958
I said no problemo.

114
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,791
Ya can see how much of
a pain in the ass this guy is.

115
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:08,291
He loves his daughter,
but he's got no social skills.

116
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:10,041
Oh yeah, like
you're one to talk.

117
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:10,833
What?

118
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:12,958
Ah! Uh, nothing, nothing!

119
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:20,583
Well here we are, finally
alone, so now you can...

120
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:23,291
Lunar!

121
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,541
Tutor me, Nagasumi!

122
00:06:28,916 --> 00:06:30,625
It's much better
for it to remain this way.

123
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:32,541
I know it is.
Yes, really.

124
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:35,000
Quit mumbling
and start tutoring me.

125
00:06:35,083 --> 00:06:35,750
We gotta make this quick!

126
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,500
Yes, of course Lunar.

127
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,041
You know, if you
really do need help

128
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:41,333
with your schoolwork,
Sun's grades

129
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:42,666
are better than mine are.

130
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,083
Us? Being tutored by
that airheaded space cadet?

131
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:47,833
Really? We'd rather die than
be humiliated in such a way.

132
00:06:47,916 --> 00:06:48,875
Honestly, we'd rather die!

133
00:06:48,958 --> 00:06:50,625
Did you have
to say it twice?

134
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:52,708
Sun's a moron
who writes all her

135
00:06:52,791 --> 00:06:54,666
answers one line off from
where they're supposed to be.

136
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,500
And then gets confused
when somehow,

137
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,375
there's an extra
question at the end!

138
00:06:58,458 --> 00:06:59,416
[SUN] Hmm?

139
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,291
Yeah, Lunar may
have a point there.

140
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:02,791
Aside from which,
we don't want Sun

141
00:07:02,875 --> 00:07:04,083
to know we're having
trouble in school.

142
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:05,500
That's unacceptable!

143
00:07:05,583 --> 00:07:07,083
She's such
a prima donna.

144
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:09,875
Now hurry up and help us
study before Sun gets back!

145
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,916
Oh yeah, a total
prima donna.

146
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,833
You'll earn penalty points
every time you talk back to us!

147
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:17,208
Okay, so go ahead
and do it! Bring it on!

148
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:19,291
Yeah?
You wanna piece of me?

149
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:21,916
'Kay, let's go!

150
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,500
[LUNAR] Oh yeah!

151
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,958
[NAGASUMI] I'm losing
my grip! I can't take it!

152
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:28,791
Tutor us and the
Grinder will stop.

153
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:31,625
Why do you care so much
about your studies, anyway?

154
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:32,875
Trust us.

155
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:34,916
This isn't exactly how
we wanted things either.

156
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,791
[LUNAR] You see,
the teacher said...

157
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:44,750
Miss Edomae, this is turning
into a serious problem.

158
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,416
Oh, come on. A pop star
doesn't really need math.

159
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:50,416
Maybe not, but it isn't
just math in this case.

160
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,416
You've gotten
zeros on everything.

161
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,500
It's unbelievable.

162
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:57,166
Are you collecting
them or something?

163
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,833
That's just mean!

164
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:00,458
We basically
steamrolled these

165
00:08:00,541 --> 00:08:02,250
people into letting
us be teachers here.

166
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:03,875
At the very least
we have to give the

167
00:08:03,958 --> 00:08:05,833
appearance of doing
our jobs correctly.

168
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:07,875
So what are you saying?

169
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,708
I'm telling you
this as a teacher.

170
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,500
If you don't
improve soon,

171
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:15,791
then I'm afraid you'll
have to, repeat the year!

172
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:16,875
NO!

173
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:17,916
[VOICES] Flunk out!

174
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,791
But I'm only
in middle school!

175
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:22,125
[MASA] No one ever
said life was fair.

176
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:23,625
Oh, you're having
study trouble?

177
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:25,250
Maybe I can help
tutor you if you want.

178
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:26,583
H-Hi, Zenigata.

179
00:08:26,666 --> 00:08:28,125
That isn't a bad idea,
Miss Edomae.

180
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,166
"Miss"?

181
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,166
Uh, what I mean is,
maybe you should

182
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,791
take Zenigata up on that offer.

183
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,291
Oh, yeah sure.

184
00:08:33,375 --> 00:08:34,458
[LUNAR THINKS] No way!

185
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:36,333
We can't ask this
wannabe cop to tutor us.

186
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:38,500
That would be humiliating!

187
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:40,708
[LUNAR] Oh, thank you so
much for the offer, really.

188
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:42,583
But all I have to do is
go back to my estate,

189
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,083
and there will be a whole team
of experts waiting to tutor me.

190
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:46,958
[MASA THINKS] Right. If she
had even one tutor at home,

191
00:08:47,041 --> 00:08:49,458
she wouldn't be
getting grades like this.

192
00:08:49,541 --> 00:08:51,041
Come to think of it, Lunar.

193
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:52,708
You mentioned
your estate just now,

194
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:55,541
but I don't think I know
where you're living.

195
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:58,875
Well, I keep it a secret,
since I'm a celebrity.

196
00:08:58,958 --> 00:09:00,041
Oh, I see.

197
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:01,958
Between the paparazzi
and the stalkers,

198
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,458
it's a lot to have to deal with.

199
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:06,125
I hadn't realized how difficult
it is being a big star.

200
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:08,166
You're right about that.
It can be rough.

201
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,041
And as a result,
I've ended up neglecting

202
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:11,916
my studies for the first time.

203
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,666
I'm always mentally
and physically

204
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,958
exhausted from my
hectic celebrity's schedule.

205
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:17,583
Stress is the
illness of our age.

206
00:09:17,666 --> 00:09:20,083
Our little spaceship
called Earth is in trouble.

207
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:21,375
I think you
lost me somewhere

208
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:23,416
around the spaceship
part of that speech.

209
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,375
But anyway, we're
classmates, so you can feel

210
00:09:25,458 --> 00:09:27,166
free to come to me with
any problem you have.

211
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,416
Oh! Thanks so much,
you're so sweet!

212
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:32,250
It means a lot to me to know
that I have a friend on my side.

213
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:34,375
[Lunar spits]

214
00:09:34,458 --> 00:09:35,708
[LUNAR THINKS] Just saying
this stuff makes us sick!

215
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:37,958
You live in a much different
world than us, girl!

216
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:40,291
And don't you forget it!

217
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:42,750
But again, I really do
appreciate the offer, I mean it!

218
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,250
Thank you so much!

219
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,166
[MAWARI] Sure.

220
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,458
Well! I'll see
you later! Okay!

221
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:51,291
Lunar has such a lovely
smile, don't you think so?

222
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:52,500
[Masa groans]

223
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:55,041
What's the point
in calling food 'lovely'?

224
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:57,333
I can go ahead
and eat you now?

225
00:09:57,416 --> 00:10:00,875
You keep up that harassment.
I'll have you arrested!

226
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,291
Okay, I get it.

227
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:10,666
Why should
someone like us

228
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:12,833
be forced to repeat
a grade in junior high?

229
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:14,291
This is a major
pain in the ass,

230
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:15,875
and we have to put
up with it because they

231
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,208
think that they can
measure a superstar,

232
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:18,958
by the same standards
as common people.

233
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:22,666
Compulsory education,
nothing you can do about it.

234
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,791
It's gotta be nice
to be so carefree.

235
00:10:24,875 --> 00:10:27,875
Hey, I am not carefree.
I'm stuck tutoring a prima donna

236
00:10:27,958 --> 00:10:29,500
who doesn't get
anything but zeros.

237
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:32,125
You're pissing me off.
Be more respectful!

238
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:33,875
You like this?
All right, here's more!

239
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:36,291
[NAGASUMI] I can never go back!
I can never go back!

240
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:39,666
[NAGASUMI] She bit
the hand that fed her.

241
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,250
Damn you manservant.

242
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,750
[NAGASUMI] Solve this by
memorizing the formula.

243
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,125
